The paper deals with visual explanations in neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the effectiveness of different methods for explaining neural network decisions, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper evaluates the impact of bias parameters, which is relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
